Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Distribution bars and the player chip grid both lived inline in
the QuizBoard render body, so every SSE delta (status, players,
answers) re-rendered both subtrees and their derived totals.

- Extract the distribution UI into a memoized Distribution
  component keyed on { dist, correctIndex }.
- Extract the player grid into a memoized PlayerList component.
- Memoize the `sorted` players array so PlayerList's props are
  referentially stable when only `dist` ticks.

Net effect: an "answers" SSE tick now only repaints the bars,
and a "players" tick only repaints the chips — not the whole
quiz board.

