+From f4719464d4189bfce2c474230348218eaa8d1d81 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: coseung2 <coseung2@users.noreply.github.com>
+Date: Sun, 12 Apr 2026 10:58:40 +0900
+Subject: [PATCH 2/3] fix: slim quiz SSE poll to deltas and per-tick counts
+ (quiz-sse-perf)
+MIME-Version: 1.0
+Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
+Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
+
+The quiz stream fired a single findUnique with a questions+answers
+join plus a full players list every second. For a 50-question,
+100-player quiz that meant thousands of hydrated rows per tick,
+even when nothing had changed.
+
+Changes:
+- Per-tick query now only reads { status, currentQ, players:
+  {id, nickname, score} }. No more questions or answers join.
+- Cache the question list once (questions are immutable during a
+  running quiz). Reset lastAnswerCount when currentQ advances so
+  distribution re-emits for the new question.
+- Track a players hash (id:score) so score-only updates actually
+  fan out — the old delta only compared player count.
+- Replace "re-emit distribution on every tick" with count() gate:
+  only when count changes do we fetch the minimal
+  { selected } findMany and recompute the 4-bucket distribution.
+- Flip `cancelled` on ReadableStream.cancel() so the recursive
+  setTimeout exits when the client disconnects instead of looping
+  forever against a closed controller.
